content.detailedDescription: Just a few hours ago at 5:37am on 17 october, 2013, i went out for a smoke.  i immediately noticed a bright stationary light in the dark sky.  this light was brighter and larger than any star in the sky and i knew it wasn't a star.  for comparison, it was at least twice the size and brightness of any star.  it was just hovering there for 5 to 10 seconds.  then it slowly winked-out or dimmed to almost nothing over a 2 second period of time.  i could barely see the light after it dimmed so much; but, i could still make out a light.  this dim light went from a stationary position to out of site in less than an additional 10 seconds.  i looked around for a bit longer, but was getting cold.  i went in the house and got a jacket and a quick bite to eat.  as soon as i came back out, directly above me, were 2 fast moving lights.  i only saw these last 2 lights for 5 seconds before they also winked-out or dimmed away to being not visible straight up overhead.  i could not see anything after they dimmed; but the sun was coming up and it was not dark enough to see a dim light.  these last 2 lights were at 6:14am.  these lights were not planes or satellites.  there was no sound for any of the lights.
content.summary: Bright light, brighter and larger than any star, hovered then dimmed to almost nothing, then quickly flew north

content.detailedDescription: I was walking home from my part-time job early this morning when it was still dark as night.  as i came into the sidewalk at my subdivision a white light that looked like a star just appeared out of nothing high above in the southwestern sky to my 11 o'clock.  it was extremely too high to be a commercial airplane and it was definitely not a helicopter.  this drew my attention immediately to keep my eyes on it as best i could.  the star like object went from white to an all solid turquoise and continued a straight flight path traveling west in a very brief hyper speed then slowed down to a normal speed until it faded away in the distance. i am not aware of any u.S.Fighter jets that uses a turquoise color, i also did not make out any wings nor any lights at the end of wings. i heard no noise and did not see the colored light object blink as a normal craft's would. i stood there in complete shock the entire time, i immediately knew i was looking at something very, very different.  so different that this is my first time feeling the need to report this to someone other then law enforcement.  it was as if a star decided to come alive and start flying, that is exactly what it looked like.  but this star went from white initially to the color i described.  i did not make out a solid structure around the light.  it was simply a flying spec of light. i've been around long enough to know what a plane, jet and helicopter looks like.  i do not want any "15 minutes of fame" or whatever, i just want to do my part as a concerned citizen to tell my sighting.  i am far from a ufo buff.
content.summary: White star like object well above commercial flight range changed to a solid turquoise color and flew in a straight path.

content.detailedDescription: Lights were shining through my windows about 11 at night ,so i went out to see what it was. i saw 2 pure white lights in the sky,one much bigger than the other moving slowly across the sky.I went inside to find my camera but could not,so i went back outside.Now there were 3 lights-1 big 2 smaller. one smaller was moving west in the opposite direction. the other small one was goig nuts circling & zig-zagging around the bigger one.About that time i heared a jet comming from the southeast,cause the objects made no noise.I thought this should be good! all of a sudden a flash came from the jet & went towards the two lights. the two took off out to sea,they were almost out of site anyway cause of trees,but the other one,going west took off,but not like a shot,but was out of site in seconds. the only thing left was the jet going out to sea.I said to myself  what the hell did i just see! this is the first time i told anybody but a couple of freinds-cause the thought i was nuts, but i knw what i saw.
content.summary: Witnessed lites in sky

content.detailedDescription:
I've seen this thing a total of four times now. with the first couple of sightings, i felt an aversion to any notion of reporting this. despite what i had witnessed, the experience still seemed like an absurdity. now, after two more sightings, i've finally settled on the need to alert others in the ufo observing community. 

it resembles a white sheet of paper, standard letter size. on three occasions it has flown directly overhead, over the south side of our parking lot at work, tracking from west to east. on two of those occasions it has arced up into the sky shortly after passing over, and on a third occasion it just continued on a straight path to the east.

with the first sighting, it paused in its trajectory and hovered directly overhead for a moment, as if it was observing me while i was looking up at it.

on one other occasion, it appeared to be engaged in the sheer joy of being able to fly. it galloped upwards in spurts, rolled over into a dive, and then leveled off while flying in a westward direction. i didn't have time to continue watching its escapades on this occasion, as it was the end of the day at work and i had to go catch my bus.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Animated flying "sheet of paper"

content.summary: Four bright red orange spheres...Thought meteor, but no trail....Five minutes apart, same trajectory

content.detailedDescription:
I never reported this incident for many reasons. in the 90's ufo's were more of a conspiracy story to most people, you were considered a kook to believe in them, which i did anyway. the only people i ever told did not believe me, including my family, so i kept it to myself. the last reason was that i could not believe i saw what i had seen and not one other person ever mentioned it. because of this, time is a little blurred.


it was spring/summer in 95 or 96(i can dig in some records to find the exact year). i lived on nowlin street in hillsboro texas. me and a couple of my room-mates had stayed up late playing video games. i was the last one standing and still enjoying my games, but really needed to take a leak. i am a guy, and lazy, so just walked out my front door to pee off the porch.
was a nice temperature being around 2ish in the morning, the night was clear as a bell as texas nights and days tend to be. no wind. the town of hillsboro has a population of about 12k at the time so it is pretty much asleep as a town, but there is people about at that time of night and interstate 35 is not a mile away. the lights of the city streets around the main street and the all night convenient stores is all the light there is, but i am one block away from that well lit main street. the night is quiet.
as i was doing my business i happen to look up. maybe it got a tad bit brighter, maybe i just flat noticed something above me, i don't know why. directly above me is a ship hull, complete with the hull plating and seam-work. the lights from the street were reflecting off the surface and was the only reason i saw it. it was not extra reflective by nature and in fact was a drab dull metal color (i am red-green color-blind). it appeared to be just 20 or 50 above the roof of the house i lived in, which had a steep roof that made it approximately equivalent to a two story place. i could be off by up to a couple dozen feet. its surface reminded me of any number of navy ships hulls.

to this day i do not know why i did not call out to my friends, not 20 feet away from me in the house and asleep, right then and there. i just took a step or two out into my yard and stared up at this huge ship flying over head. something so amazing that it has to be shared and i just watch it fly away.

it made absolutely no sound, not a single light of its own was showing moving slowly to the north. it grows in width as it goes overhead and when the what i assume was the back end came into view i knew it was triangular shaped and where the lights of the street no longer reflected was the blackness of its hull as it blocked out starlight for a while.

it just kept going north. no other change in direction, action, or mode.

i told my friends and wife at the time. never heard mention of it or any rumors of something weird. as far as i know, i am the only person that saw it. i could have called them out there and i didn't. i never could explain to myself why i did not chase after it in the car, wake my friends, run down the street after it to see where it went, anything.

others are seeing something that sounds like mine in texas now, so i thought i would put in what i knew.
content.summary: Large, dark, triangular shaped craft flying low over hillsboro texas 1995

content.detailedDescription: Globe, az near highway 60 and 3rd street.  first time i saw the bright orange lights it  was  at about 6:50  pm looking west above pinal mountains .  no clouds, moon was up. three large round bright orange lights in a horizontal line flashed on for about 2 seconds then fizzled out. then 2 orange lights flashed on then off, then one light on then off. they were above the horizon about 45degrees moving together (like on the side of a blimp) slowly from left to right (south to north) also saw jets flying north and south around the lights.  thought the lights came from the jets, but they were so much bigger than the white flashing lights from the jets so i thought it was a ufo!  my niece came out and we walked to the circle k on highway 60 and 7th street.  on the way back at 7:25 we saw and heard jets flying around.  looking west again saw the three bright orange lights appear then dissappear, then two then one. my niece only saw the last light. we both saw four jets in the shape of a square flew north made 180 degree turn together then east overhead,  then turned north and back past me to the west.  saw 4 to 6 jets circling the area for about 20 minutes.  we got home, went inside and told my husband.   felt curious and a little scared.  he came outside and we watched the jets making huge circles around globe. i got my phone to make  a video.  walked out into the middle of the street looking south east at about 7:50  i saw them again, same sequence but this time they seemed closer.  the orange lights went out like fireworks fizzling out. this time they were moving together slowly from right to left (south to north)  i strained to see if there was anything there after the lights were gone, saw only small white lights from jets.  it happened too fast to get a video.  my husband walked out and saw the last light (just one orange ball light up and disappear).  we stood outside for about 15 minutes and saw jets flying back and forth (north and south, then overhead to the west then back to the east.
content.summary: Three large orange lights in straight line lit up for a feww seconds then disappeared

content.detailedDescription:
This is an incident i witnessed as a 6 year old boy. we lived at [address removed/cms/tg]. grand island, ne. the neighborhood was fairly new at the time and compared to today, was on the fringes of several farms and quasi-rural. the northern major road running east/west was capitol ave. and one block south was state st. young kids in the neighborhood attended west lawn elementary (not the new one, but rather the old one at state st. & broadwell).
 
this is the view looking to the north on [street name removed/cms/tg] which was right in front of our house. there were not many trees back then as the neighborhood was very new. there were even fewer houses. most of the houses feature here on the right were not built until 1965/1966. so the view northward was very open and clear all the way up to capitol.
on saturday, august 8th, 1964 a lot of the neighborhood kids and i were out playing in the street. it was typical stuff; riding bikes, playing army, simply running all over the place. a lot of parents were out working on their yards, washing their cars, etc. just a typical hot and very humid day in central nebraska.  an object drifted over the sky, transiting nw to se on its flight path. it got everyone���s attention pretty quick. it was huge. far bigger than a modern airship or similar type of craft. it was slightly overcast that day, but you could see it clearly. it was black, shaped like an oval cylinder. it had a red line going around the middle of it that was lit up and appeared almost electrical in nature. i remember smelling ozone. like you do when you short a wire out or with lightning. at the bottom and slightly to the side was some type of opening or even possibly a light source that was intense blue-white. it was not a bean or anything, at least it did not appear that way. it makes me think it was an opening as it appeared and then disappeared a couple of times. i do not recall anything coming out of it. but there was a strange sound, almost like ringing in your ears ��� but it was a really high frequency. it didn���t hurt or anything, but it was there.

people were talking about it and my dad (who cannot remember it happening) said it was probably some kind of usaf aircraft. one of the neighbors, my friend [name removed/cms/tg]��� grandfather thought it was probably something the russians had cooked up to scare people with. the odd thing in this was the longer it hovered there, the more quiet everyone got and soon stopped talking altogether. they just stared at it. even my friend "d" and another friend, a girl named "p" stopped talking and just stared at it. no one spoke, no one moved. i think at some point that the same happened to me.

i have no recollection of time between the incident and sunday dinner, which was the next day. i do not know what happened in that time period, as the next day we were getting in my dad���s valiant and heading over to my grandmother���s house on [street name removed/cms/tg].
 
this is approximately what the object looked like. i am guessing here, but i believe it may have been as large as a ��� mile in length. it was simply massive.

most of the kids there that day are haunted by this incident. they know it happened, but none of the adults remember anything at all. it is like their memories were erased. this has haunted me for 50 years. i remember it as clear as daylight.
content.summary: Unknown ufo - memory loss

content.detailedDescription:
My wife and i were sitting outside enjoying the clear night and calm weather. i had just thought to myself "it would be a good night to see a ufo" it was so clear. next and within about 30 seconds my wife noticed a orange light traveling toward us coming from the ne. i had not shared my earlier thought with her yet. we both stood up and i almost immediately started to use my video phone. the object glowed an orange color with light traces of red inside it. it traveled at a steady speed and appeared never to change direction or altitude. 

my first thoughts was a ufo or if not what is it? my wife says her first thought was a meteor or shooting star, now she is unsure and talks about it less than i do. she is not as open to sharing our story until i start to tell someone. it was no big deal to her.

my odd thoughts on the whole experience is that i had just thought about seeing a ufo and during the experience i thought of jellyfish. i think the jellyfish thought came because the objects illumination was iridescent similar to the videos i have seen of jellyfish, not a light that looked like it was from a normal light source. the color spectrum of the light was different somehow?

i also was amazed that i didn't want to stay up all night and stare at the night sky searching for more objects. i was tired and all but it was weird it didn't fire me up and have me laying flat on my back on a blanket or looking straight up into the vast unknown. i do remember thinking it may be a thousand years before another object passes over our yard. i stayed up about an hour then calmly went inside and went to sleep. 

p.S. look for the red object (it was orange to us at the time) the large white object is the moon.
i am not a video expert, this is obvious after you watch it. the video is pretty low quality and shaky but it is all i had on short notice. i hope someone with video experience can somehow salvage something useful from it. please let me know if the video is determined to be an identified object or not?
i used profanity in the video  ...To those that may be offended; sorry ahead of time.
content.summary: Moon could be used for a size reference. orange oval object traveling in a straight line at a steady speed. no detectable sound or emissions. orange colored light resembled a jellyfish glow.

��� the sighting occurred last night, october 14, 2013, in se ireland (county wexford), a half mile from a residence at the foot of the blackstairs mountains.
��� it occurred at twilight, around 8pm. i had made a small fire in the woods about 3/4 of a mile from the house i'm staying at, and was walking back to the house to make dinner and because i was without a flashlight.
��� the object/light was glowing as bright as the moon, giving off a whitish/yellow light. it's glow was constant and it did not flash, flicker, or emit multiple colors of light. 
��� due to its luminosity, i could not distinguish the outline of any craft, but it's shape or the light emitted was round���circular, not elliptical. 
��� it's size, to the eye, was roughly that of a pencil eraser if held at an arm length from the body.
��� it moved in a straight path from west to east���it did not wobble, bounce, or display pendulum-like movement. 
��� it was completely silent, and there was no condensation or vapor trail of any kind.
��� it's altitude appeared to be between 5,000-8,000ft; shortly after the sighting, a commercial jet flew overhead at a much higher altitude���this offered additional reference regarding the altitude of the anomalous sighting.
���it appeared to be moving 2-3 times faster than a commercial jet (to the eye, without regard to altitude); again, it appeared to be much lower and was completely silent. as it continued on it's path, it's size and brightness gradually diminished.
��� 3/4 of the way into it's path from horizon-to-horizon, it simply disappeared; it could be possible that, although abrupt, it became 'invisible' due to its distance, the angle of view, and atmospheric perspective
���the sighting lasted for approximately 60-90 sec. 
��� it was absolutely not a comet, weather balloon, or misidentification of the planet venus. 
��� it did not appear to be an iridium flare, as i have seen several of these. unlike iridium flares (which display intermittent variation in brightness), this object/light had a constant, even luminance. 

xx
content.summary: Silent, very bright light moving on a straight easterly-course. se ireland, wexford county.

content.detailedDescription:
When i was in branson on 10-7-13 trout fishing on taneycomo with my best friend and his wife, i noticed a jet flying overhead that had an unusual con trail.  it was wide as it came out of the jet and tapered off to a point as it trailed, but it left a perfect eye at the wide end that made it look exactly like a needle.  i thought this would make a good picture so i took three pictures in succession with my iphone just to make sure one came out good.  it was 10:20 am. unfortunately, the eye of the needle didn���t come out in any of the pictures and i was disappointed.  but when i looked closely at the third picture i saw something that i didn't see in the first two pictures that i took. it was lower than the jet and just off the horizon and looked like a perfect triangle.  i also noticed a very faint trail from the lower left point of the triangle going down at an angle. i had not noticed it in the first two pictures so i went back and examined them closely. there was nothing in the first photo but when i zoomed in on the second photo right at the horizon, i located the triangle again, but much fainter. without overlaying the photos, it appeared to be at a direct angle down from the faint trail left by the triangle in the third photo. the triangle had not been visible to the naked eye when watching the con trail. 

the first three photos that i have attached are the three photos i took and are in order. the forth photo is the triangle in photo three zoomed in and circled.  the fifth photo is the photo two with the triangle circled at the horizon. 

my first thought upon seeing the triangle in photo three was a reflection from the sun. but upon locating the triangle in photo two in a different location and nothing in the first photo, i have ruled that out and will wait for an expert opinion. all the photos were taken in rapid succession and without any change of camera position. i will be anxious to know what the experts think.

thank you,

paul ericsson
lebanon, mo
content.summary: I took three photos of a jet con trail and located a triangle in two of the photos which had not been visible to naked eye.
